\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 I didn't know many of them at all, never went to church. Not having gone myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 So you don't know who in Keighley went to the church, who were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 considered}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  church people and those who were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 considered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes. The Tories of course went to the Church of England in the main and the Liberals went to the Non-Conformist. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Would you say they were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 healthy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  set of people who went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They were wealthy in both instances. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Just politically they were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within the working class, I think you've mentioned this already really, that the
re was a class similar to your own and a lower class of people who were labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Labourers and so on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Can you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347  differentiate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  the lives of these two and what sort of people fitted into the two categories, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
 were mainly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 skilled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  were they in your case?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Well in the street that I liked in I should say that the whole lot of them were - of the men were skilled in some occupation or }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 . So I didn't come in contact with the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They lived away from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Could you describe a family in each group, a family that you knew that would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 typify}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  your sort of set of working class and the poorer set of working class, could you describe to families to illustrate the differences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Be rather difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 You can't just think of a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
You can't think of the differences in the way of life, or sort of houses they lived in or what their children had to wear in these cases or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 In the very poor - places - they - as I've mentioned bef
ore, the people living in Eastwood Square, which was at the time I went to school considered very poor, it wasn't necessarily - it didn't necessarily }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10042093\charrsid2571347 relate }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10042093\charrsid2571347 every}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
 house that but it did to the majority. The only difference there was there was poor houses
 and very little furnishings in them I should imagine and - they used to buy their - their meat and stuff like that by going to the markets late at Saturday night because there was no refrigeration in those days so the butchers had got to get shut, the sa
m
e applied to vegetables and soon and so they could buy it cheaper by going late. By late I mean eleven o'clock or turned on Saturday night. I'm not saying they got worse fed but they got this stuff cheaper, you see, than by going on a Saturday afternoon a
nd buying your meat and vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 A family in your own group would mainly shop Saturday afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They wouldn't go to this trouble of going down late Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Some of them were extremely poor of course and - I should imagine that - although I don't know any particular case but it }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 certainly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  must have applied at Eastwood school that some of them would be - some of the children'd definitely be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 hungry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  because there was no - there was no means of - getting school meals or anything like that in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do you remember, were these poorer children clothed adequa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 ely or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, they were very poorly clothed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Did they always have shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No. Some of them - clogs with broken soles and stuff like that. Wet feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 What would you put this poverty down to, was it the amount of money the parents earned or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Well they didn't earn a very great deal and - a lot of them were outdoor workers, what I mean in the building trade. Now in the winter mont
hs of course they were off work and there was no such thing as falling back on the Labour Exchange because the Labour Exchange wasn't in existence in those days. So - they weren't members of a union or anything like that so their income was nil. They had 
then to go to the - workhouse. To get relief you see, which was - probably - a very small amount they got. Just - just about - just a matter of keeping them alive and nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Were they given money to buy food or were they actually given food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
I think they were given, I'm not certain of this because - never having had it to do but I think they were given tickets which they could get food with, see. Sort of tokens to take to certain grocers and then they'd get food with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 What sort of houses did these people live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Mostly back to back houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They were quite old houses were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Quite old houses, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 What sort of houses were the people of your own group living in at that time, were they back to back houses as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, they were - they were through houses built about 1895.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Comparatively new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They were much newer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347  than tho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 se ones }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  the poorer people were living in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Can you think of any other factors such as drinking 
or any thing like that that contributed to the poverty of these people in the backs to backs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
Only the fact of course as I've said that they - they had nothing to fall back on. Yes, I think it was - they got into a position where - they were miserabl
e and if they got any money well - they thought if they got some drink it'd cheer them up a bit and of course, as I said before, it's a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  circle and - they eventually got worse off with it and the people who suffered most were the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest, did your own group feel this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 We def - we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 definitely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  thought we were better off than those who lived in Eastwood Square or down side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Which families did you think of as being rough, were they just the ones round Eastwood Square?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, you - you pick families out in most streets, they'd -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Can you think of a particular family that was thought of as being rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
They were mostly aggressive children you see. Fighting and stuff like that and - giving a lot of cheek back to their elders and stuff like that. They were considered the rough ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Children that today you consider as being in need of care and protection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 More or less, yes. But they weren't thieves or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Were there other families in the neighbourhood that were thought of as being respectable particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Well some was thought about being a bit snooty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 You can't think of any families that the rest of the neighbourhood had more respect for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, I can't think of that, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Which families would you say you considered a bit snooty?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12265633\charrsid2571347 Well there\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  be - in some cases they were one with 
- one child who they attempted to dress considerably better than anyone else in the street, such things as that. It was only - I don't say the parents thought the same thing, I mean it was the - children who thought this. Or else you - or else he or she w
as a little clever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15925974\charrsid2571347 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 loke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Because he dressed better than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15925974\charrsid2571347 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  the craftsmen and labourers living immediately round you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 I - I don't think that a single labouring family lived in that street I No, not one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Or nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, not that I'm aware of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 So this was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15925974\charrsid2571347 distinction}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 , that labourers mainly lived in another area
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes, you see, parents made a desperate effort in those day
s to get their a - an apprenticeship and that was one of the main things and - and there generation came up there was these craftsmen families. I'm not saying }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10042093\charrsid2571347 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  went to engineering, they went in textiles and - any amount of trades.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different \{ILLEGIBLE\}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 I think so generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They didn't treat them differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another, if so can you remember anyone who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, I can't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 The classes were fairly definitely settled?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 You don't remember any children at that time growing up and mo
ving into your area from the Eastwood Square area or moving from your area into a better class area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, I can't say I do. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Getting better jobs or becoming wealthy or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Not to me by my parents anyway I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Can you remember other people in the neighbourhood describing people as real gentlemen and real ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Some of the neighbours may have thought that - the - employing classes were real ladies and real gentlemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Why do you think they thought this, was it because of their way of life or the way they treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15925974\charrsid2571347 I think it was the - because they lived in considerably better surroundings more than anything.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 What sort of houses did they live in to inspire this, were they very large houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They were very large houses, you've got, as I've mentioned before, Strong Close, Cliff Castle, Red Holt. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 These were very large houses weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Very large. The Knowle down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 They were set in more or less parks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 All in park grounds, yes. Yes. Yes. Every one of those I've mentioned they're owned by a manufacturing class, the wool trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 The people who owned large woolen mills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 And accumulated large fortunes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 This was why the people felt they must be real ladies and real gentlemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Because they lived in these large houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 That's right. And they were equally divided between Tories and Labour - between Tories and - Conservatives - Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 The people who lived in the large houses weren't all politically the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, not by any means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do I remember seeing a policeman? Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 What did you think of him? When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No. No, she never said that. The policeman, as far as we were concerned - was somebody we kept out of
 the way of. If we were playing ball and - on the road or anything like that they picked it up and run. I should imagine since I've grown up much to his amusement. If he caught you doing anything which you shouldn't be doing, well - he'd put his hand down
 the back of your collar and give you a good shaking and send you home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 So you were a little bit in awe of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Very well. Very well. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 He wasn't harsh at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 He wasn't constantly reporting people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Oh no not by any means
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 He was a friend more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Your home wasn't rented, your father bought it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Bought it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Never occurred to me in those days as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Looking back now you feel that they probably had to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Probably had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 So you had no thought on the matter because it didn't occur to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 
Well I can't remember him being ill. I should say that it made no difference. Well of course there was - at that period the insurance acts had come in. He was a member of a trades union and s
o - by the time he'd drawn from different sources he probably have very near as much as he had for working a full week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 That was the time of the depression?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes. Yes. But you see, being - as I say, he was a member of a trades union at that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10042093\charrsid2571347 time that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  paid out his unemployment benefit. And he'd get his state benefit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 That would be in the '20's wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 So you don't remember him being out of work either for illness or any other reason prior to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 W
hen there was someone in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it, do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 You don't remember any family being disapproved of in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 No, I do not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 My father would. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 That was before you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Yes, the three R's. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10042093\charrsid2571347 Could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347  you read or write or anything before you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3165056 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 I could read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433480 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6961456\charrsid2571347 Before you started school?
